commit_message:
Revert "[config-ref] Remove cisco FC Zone manager driver"

The Cisco FCZM driver was removed for lack of CI during the Mitaka
development cycle. Prior to the final Mitaka release this was
rectified and the FCZM driver was added back in to the release.
This cisco FCZM driver doc should be added again

This reverts commit c2ed9b27819043c0b7e109bbb355cf3b36ed7c05.

backport: mitaka

Change-Id: Ibe0d72d1070fcc49194c488806c71a0423df790b
(cherry picked from commit c44f9a3282e3a3da3701e14e01bdc7a1a1b4faab)

commit_message:
Remove duplicate definition for extension drivers

The parameter for ml2/extension driver had not previously been
defined, so it was defined here for Nexus 1000V. Now that it is
present, this is a duplicate definition that needs to be removed.

Also adding missing spec file for Nexus1000V. Edited spec slightly
to fix failing test cases in Liberty.

commit_message:
Run amphora haproxy in a network namespace

In the current Octavia there is the possibility of an address
space conflict between the Octavia load balancer management
network and a tenant network.
This patch puts the haproxy processes inside the amphora into
a network namespace to provide isolation from the load balancer
management network.

A new file /var/lib/octavia/plugged_interfaces is created and
interfaces are writted to it on every plugVIP or plugNetwork call.
Interfaces in this file are created under the network namespace.

Change-Id: I75472885fe45226a5315867369eaef9b001a112b
Co-Authored-By: Bharath M <bharath.stacker@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: #1458920
(cherry picked from commit b89abe18718964f53b463a723551ce73673ee135)

commit_message:
don't set libvirt cpu_model

Nova was incorrectly checking cpu model compatiblity when running qemu
guests, which isn't needed, as they can emulate any instruction under
the sun. This removes this setting from our testing after Nova lands a
patch to fix this.

Depends-On: I8b782678a6dfa7bcfc203381037e1df4475c3194

Change-Id: I41b4c0371515c88d4ab9fc127e5abc9b3fb97f31

commit_message:
Add upper constraints to glanceclient

This will force pip install to use the upper-constraints.txt specified
version of pip modules. When you don't do this, you are out on the
bleeding edge and become unstable everytime some python library in the
world changes in a way that you don't expect.

The script is needed because it cleans up the conflicting entry that
corresponds to the client before applying it to source based installation.

Change-Id: I8f168fde04bf9e421d9a39e91a041512bf4f2b79
Closes-Bug: 1563038

commit_message:
Prevent keystone eventlet from starting

On debian based hosts, when a package is installed, the packager
has the service automatically start. This causes a problem,
especially in CI, where the eventlet doesnt quit fast enough
and apache is started but cant bind to port.

Change-Id: I6b07a70f0729639f12ebc19f9d3cd405d8be214b
Closes-Bug: 1569390
(cherry picked from commit 78ef8e9ad49249587bcf399d9076a084d8ceea7f)

commit_message:
Rename ansible-puppet to ansible-role-puppet

The common practice upstream and also with all of the other roles in
OpenStack is to prefix them with "ansible-role-". Ansible Galaxy is able
to detect that a repo named thusly is a role. Also, maybe this will make
ansible-puppet and puppet-ansible less confusing.

Change-Id: I889399813748919ce1788ad18ce84c3894e12ab1

commit_message:
Rename openstack-ansible-ironic to openstack-ansible-os_ironic

In order to ensure that all OpenStack Service roles are named with
the same convention (using the 'os_' prefix) and therefore allow
the deployment tooling to react to the roles in the same way for
production wheel repo building, we ask for the rename of the
OpenStack-Ansible Ironic repository.

As this deliverable is important to have as part of our Mitaka
release, we'll be tagging prior to the Newton summit. As such we'll
be using the GitHub URL for this repo (it'll handle the rename
redirect) in all code that refers to it to ensure that the tags can
build before and after the rename.

That said, it would be preferred to handle the rename prior to the
first tag so if it's possible to get it done prior to the summit
then we can consider holding off doing the tag until the rename is
complete.

Needed-By: I2ab80e4fdb413d469c7aa65e5f018b66cc203b7c
Change-Id: Ieeff38d029c592ced7a1ab4bc1af42f3ff1e9fcd

commit_message:
Enable Mistral execution cleanup

Update the Mistral settings for the engine so that we allow old
(finished) execution to be automatically cleaned up after they
are 2 days old. The cleanup check is performed by the Mistral
engine process every 2 hours.

commit_message:
Raise an exception if no active VIOSes in build_tx_feed_task

get_active_vioses returns an empty list if there aren't any
active VIOSes. If an empty list is used as the feed to a FeedTask
then we get a generic error explaining that the FeedTask can't have
an empty feed.

This change attempts to make the error more clear in the event
there aren't any active VIOSes when build_tx_feed_task is called
by raising an exception explaining that there aren't any active
VIOSes.

Change-Id: I3d67c653131952bfc13bbbda2e67486c0291c4cc
Closes-Bug: #1581652
(cherry picked from commit 0b2125e64c628c90633b08dbe4033bcbb5fafe92)

subject: crypto - make some probe tests compatible with crypto
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-05-19 15:54:08.000000000', 'files': ['test/probe/test_container_merge_policy_index.py', 'test/probe/test_empty_device_handoff.py', 'test/probe/test_object_handoff.py', 'test/probe/test_object_failures.py'], 'message': 'crypto - make some probe tests compatible with crypto

Tests in these modules:

  test_empty_device_handoff.py
  test_object_failures.py
  test_object_handoff.py

previously failed when the crypto middlewares were enabled in the
proxy pipeline. This was because they make assertions about the state
of the on disk object data and etag value based on making direct GETs
to the object servers using direct_client. When crypto is enabled the
on disk content is unknown and not equal to the PUT object plaintext,
so these assertions fail.

We can avoid the failures without needing to require encryption
to be disabled by comparing values of the on disk data "before"
and "after" the test operations rather than comparing "after"
values to an absolute value.

Tests in test_container_merge_policy_index.py passed with crypto
middleware but were using an internal client to put and get objects.
This patch changes those tests to use an external client to put/get
objects so that encryption is used (if installed) and also adds
assertions to check that objects moved by the container reconciler
are not corrupted.

Probe tests in test_container_sync.py may still fail due to the
container sync not having the crypto middlewares configured in
its internal client.

Change-Id: I640c7e738c8a553030d9ed58a953dd3eead0aa07
'}]
commit_message:
crypto - make some probe tests compatible with crypto

Tests in these modules:

  test_empty_device_handoff.py
  test_object_failures.py
  test_object_handoff.py

previously failed when the crypto middlewares were enabled in the
proxy pipeline. This was because they make assertions about the state
of the on disk object data and etag value based on making direct GETs
to the object servers using direct_client. When crypto is enabled the
on disk content is unknown and not equal to the PUT object plaintext,
so these assertions fail.

We can avoid the failures without needing to require encryption
to be disabled by comparing values of the on disk data "before"
and "after" the test operations rather than comparing "after"
values to an absolute value.

Tests in test_container_merge_policy_index.py passed with crypto
middleware but were using an internal client to put and get objects.
This patch changes those tests to use an external client to put/get
objects so that encryption is used (if installed) and also adds
assertions to check that objects moved by the container reconciler
are not corrupted.

Probe tests in test_container_sync.py may still fail due to the
container sync not having the crypto middlewares configured in
its internal client.

Change-Id: I640c7e738c8a553030d9ed58a953dd3eead0aa07

One of the common use cases for the admin_token middleware was to
provide a recovery mechanism for cloud operators that had accidentally

Instead of using bootstrap to create a second admin just to recover the

Closes-Bug: 1588860
"}]
commit_message:
Bootstrap: enable and reset password for existing users

One of the common use cases for the admin_token middleware was to
provide a recovery mechanism for cloud operators that had accidentally
disabled themselves or lost their password.

Instead of using bootstrap to create a second admin just to recover the
first, this change allows bootstrap to reset the user's credentials and
ensure that the account is enabled.

Change-Id: I82cafced67852335e9bb49035f13c993c7ccd2df
Closes-Bug: 1588860

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-02 10:20:41.000000000', 'files': ['sahara/conductor/manager.py'], 'message': "Fix cluster creation with another tenant

This patch fix cluster creation with public template that has been
created in another tenant (not in current).
The problem is that at the particular time configs of cluster and node
groups are merging. And 'tenant_id' property of node group replaces the
same property of cluster config. Therefore, further sahara db api
cannot find this new cluster with current tenant id if node group has
been created in another tenant.

Change-Id: I8eaa4350ec873cca73a6e828efd54200912bacaa
closes-bug: 1585211
(cherry picked from commit b9b2dca4f95340d932f40e1e2be5982efbf81523)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix cluster creation with another tenant

This patch fix cluster creation with public template that has been
created in another tenant (not in current).
The problem is that at the particular time configs of cluster and node
groups are merging. And 'tenant_id' property of node group replaces the
same property of cluster config. Therefore, further sahara db api
cannot find this new cluster with current tenant id if node group has
been created in another tenant.

Change-Id: I8eaa4350ec873cca73a6e828efd54200912bacaa
closes-bug: 1585211
(cherry picked from commit b9b2dca4f95340d932f40e1e2be5982efbf81523)

revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2016-06-01 17:42:43.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/test-bifrost-venv.sh', 'scripts/README.md', 'scripts/test-bifrost-inventory-dhcp.sh', 'scripts/test-bifrost.sh', 'scripts/test-bifrost-build-images.sh'], 'message': 'Unify testing scripts

We previously had four separate test scripts to control basic
tests, tests where bifrost and its dependencies install into
a virtual environment, tests where bifrost builds a deployment image,
and tests where bifrost uses DHCP. This resulted in the scripts getting
out of sync with one another as changes were made. In order to increase
consistency in testing and improve maintainability, consolidate the three
scripts into test-bifrost.sh, add symlinks where the other scripts were,
and update the documentation.

Change-Id: Ic005960d00a145fc7b28ed423fb8f92e41d7ef0b
'}]
commit_message:
Unify testing scripts

We previously had four separate test scripts to control basic
tests, tests where bifrost and its dependencies install into
a virtual environment, tests where bifrost builds a deployment image,
and tests where bifrost uses DHCP. This resulted in the scripts getting
out of sync with one another as changes were made. In order to increase
consistency in testing and improve maintainability, consolidate the three
scripts into test-bifrost.sh, add symlinks where the other scripts were,
and update the documentation.

Change-Id: Ic005960d00a145fc7b28ed423fb8f92e41d7ef0b

commit_message:
Remove invalid directory_mode from ironic install

As part of the ironic install, when copying the ironic rootwrap.d config
we set directory_mode: yes. This is meant to be an octal value and also
has a reasonable default so we really should not be setting it.

Change-Id: Ie1a8be4e2436bda08f33117d1795ea713003c224

commit_message:
Add DefCore guideline gate checks for json lint and schema

Currently DefCore does not gate against valid json, either through
linting or schema checking. This patch adds checks both and rejects
changes to the active and next guidelines that do not pass either
linting or schema checking.

Change-Id: I27ce6e36ef8627402fea79b2ee1d94dac42511cb
Depends-On: I13ee6b16115588527fde070e34874edf919aa864

commit_message:
Deployment and provision Nailgun tasks is now run asynchrously

Deployment and provisioning preparations could last a long when Fuel is
working with a hundreds of nodes. But operator should be able to
observe cluster state and operate other clusters.

Change-Id: I73802c91f93a46855b006cb05a8b5722109e9e6a
Partial-Bug: #1569859

commit_message:
Always wait for database backend

Previously when using the detached-database functionality, the various
tasks that require the database task on the primary controller will run
immediately after the primary controller database task has executed.
Because the wait for the mysql backend was included within the enabled
if block, when detached db is used the database task finishes
immediately without the database actually being ready. This change
takes the mysql backend wait code and puts it in it's own class that
can be included anywhere the mysql backend wait needs to occur.
Additionally this code can be leveraged as a task if necessary.

Change-Id: Ia1d45f45cbbd91b7c6cacd4aa46dae0a92e4156e
Closes-Bug: #1588387
(cherry picked from commit 39ba427e5fd03f8b69fe2109c0bbb4ee4748a70f)

commit_message:
Fixed help messages for path_mtu and global_physnet_mtus options

For path_mtu, make it clear it applies to tunnel typed tenant networks.
Removed information about specific mechanisms used to advertise MTU
values to instances because a) it duplicates the global_physnet_mtu
option description; b) it is not complete now that we also advertise MTU
via RAs. Finally, removed description for calculation details because
they duplicate global_physnet_mtu description.

While at it, fixed help text for global_physnet_mtus option not to refer
to segment_mtu which was renamed into global_physnet_mtu lately.

The cherry-pick differs from the master patch, as Mitaka still uses
a default value of 1500 for path_mtu. Master uses 0. The effect is,
that with Mitaka you have to override the default 1500 path_mtu
value to use jumbo frames, while with master the default 0 value is
being ignored. There it's sufficient to specify the global_physnet_mtu
only.

Change-Id: Ib0010206f08ec9a76b0e26e84cdb03c80755908d
Related-Bug: #1566706
(cherry picked from commit 403e5a07f51dee1efd335011cdd6b4454d1e7fde)

commit_message:
Make deepcopy of update body in API layer

This adjusts the update handler in the API layer to pass a deepcopy
of the original update body to ensure that the original is used on
any generated retry requests.

Without this update handlers that modified the body as they processed
it (e.g. the external gateway update for routers) would be missing
data on a retry request.

This adds a test case for the bug that was caused by this.

Closes-Bug: #1584920
Change-Id: I88fb9d45eb82ef48e0d865decdcc7fad1c5fb361
(cherry picked from commit 5109d16bc52abb20636c94c0208fb498d1c626eb)

PEP257's D203 check ensures that you have a blank line before class

commit_message:
PEP257: Ignore D203 because it was deprecated

PEP257's D203 check ensures that you have a blank line before class
docstrings. This rule directly conflicts with D211 (no blank lines
before class docstrings), which is intended to supersede D203.

The original language in PEP257 which D203 was based on was actually
removed from PEP257 by Guido here:

  https://hg.python.org/peps/rev/9b715d8246db

Change-Id: Icc048b947acea8f655d00540c221123b906e7545

commit_message:
PEP257: Ignore D203 because it was deprecated

PEP257's D203 check ensures that you have a blank line before class
docstrings. This rule directly conflicts with D211 (no blank lines
before class docstrings), which is intended to supersede D203.

The original language in PEP257 which D203 was based on was actually
removed from PEP257 by Guido here:

  https://hg.python.org/peps/rev/9b715d8246db

Change-Id: Icc048b947acea8f655d00540c221123b906e7545

subject: Use JQuery promise/deferred objects to track AJAX
revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2015-12-09 16:38:46.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.communication.js', 'horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.tables.js'], 'message': 'Use JQuery promise/deferred objects to track AJAX

The JQuery library offers objects known as deferred for tracking
multiple call backs, this can be used with AJAX to track cases when we
only want to do something once multiple requests are complete such as
re-calling the datatables update method.

This also allows for us to track the completed state of a request in the
ajax queue without injecting a custom completed callback into every
request that is handled by the queue.

Change-Id: I7d5acb6d05a5822b2de7d73678797166276ac599
Closes-Bug: 1442146
'}]
commit_message:
Use JQuery promise/deferred objects to track AJAX

The JQuery library offers objects known as deferred for tracking
multiple call backs, this can be used with AJAX to track cases when we
only want to do something once multiple requests are complete such as
re-calling the datatables update method.

This also allows for us to track the completed state of a request in the
ajax queue without injecting a custom completed callback into every
request that is handled by the queue.

Change-Id: I7d5acb6d05a5822b2de7d73678797166276ac599
Closes-Bug: 1442146

subject: Fix the py34 jenkins job
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-06-02 04:40:36.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt'], 'message': "Fix the py34 jenkins job

The oslo.messaging<5.2.0(the v5.2.0 update change is in review[1])
depends on amqp>=1.4.0, in amqp-2.0 and amqp2.0.1, there is an issue[2]
that lead the amqp cannot be correctly installed in py34
environment(the depent package vine-1.1.0 of amqp won't bee installed),
that has borken the ceilometer py34 job[3]. we can wait the change[1]
merged and then bump the oslo.message version to avoid this issue. Because
Ceilometer don't participate the global-requirements, so we bump the
oslo.messaging to 5.2.0.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/324023/
[2] https://github.com/celery/py-amqp/issues/91
[3] http://logs.openstack.org/41/323641/4/check/gate-ceilometer-python34/cf3f043/console.html

Change-Id: Icb34a7f0e03662868aa0ce6e060c5e951711b79e
"}]
commit_message:
Fix the py34 jenkins job

The oslo.messaging<5.2.0(the v5.2.0 update change is in review[1])
depends on amqp>=1.4.0, in amqp-2.0 and amqp2.0.1, there is an issue[2]
that lead the amqp cannot be correctly installed in py34
environment(the depent package vine-1.1.0 of amqp won't bee installed),
that has borken the ceilometer py34 job[3]. we can wait the change[1]
merged and then bump the oslo.message version to avoid this issue. Because
Ceilometer don't participate the global-requirements, so we bump the
oslo.messaging to 5.2.0.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/324023/
[2] https://github.com/celery/py-amqp/issues/91
[3] http://logs.openstack.org/41/323641/4/check/gate-ceilometer-python34/cf3f043/console.html

Change-Id: Icb34a7f0e03662868aa0ce6e060c5e951711b79e

commit_message:
Fix role restriction iteration cycle according to docs

Role restrictions could be defined in full or short format

restrictions:
  - condition: "settings:other_plugin == null or settings:other_plugin.metadata.enabled != true"
    message: "Other plugin must be installed and enabled"
  - "settings:common.libvirt_type.value != 'kvm'": "KVM only is supported"
  - "settings:storage.volumes_ceph.value == true"

This patch fixes restriction iteration cycle.

Change-Id: I6072ea9e92999ae7a94f28f42bb475b30bb7fff1
Closes-Bug: #1586334

commit_message:
Update all SHAs for 13.1.3

This patch updates all the roles to the latest available stable
SHA's, updates all the OpenStack Service SHA's and also updates
the appropriate python requirements pins.

The tempest SHA is set to c2c90574a78c7704f06e8fac279c4f1d11365993
in order to work around a mismatch between the tempest requirements
and the upper constraints for the paramiko python package.

Change-Id: Id2556dff54f153bd4f3018f95b9d6f77a016d541

commit_message:
Fix tempest tests that use SSL

A new version of gabbi, 1.21.0, is required for gnocchi to work
properly with live SSL tests. That version adds a require_ssl
arg to build_tests. These changes determine the correct value
for that, and set it.

Change-Id: If8e1b0ae7de5d01c3e29de639474bc893fd7eb37

commit_message:
Fix mistral installation in devstack

After pip upgrading following error has occured during
mistral installation:
Invalid requirement, parse error at "'[-e]'"

I assume that this is because of extra '-e' flag that was passed
in mistral script and that is redundant ('-e' flag will be added
automatically in setup_develop function).

Change-Id: Ifed16935b045c723881a9da157a8759eea421c2c
(cherry picked from commit 2b517d8838e1ebfa1a4ea45c7c2d92ee2c1076c4)

commit_message:
Handle ovs_socket_mem as list

Due to yaml dump/load incomsistency, string like '1,2,3,4' will be
dumped without quotes and loaded without commas. To fix it, socket
memory per NUMA will be passed as a list.

Change-Id: I579c43a0e8a391092f33a755e18b06ef8ed1a62e
Closes-Bug: #1587898
(cherry picked from commit a91ea7a30900714aabfb8249d2d5f5b9c2131243)

commit_message:
Versioned notification for keypairs

Currently, no useful notification will be sent
for keypair state change.
This spec will transform legacy notification
to versioned notification about keypairs,
and at the same time extend contents of
notification with extra data.

Blueprint: keypair-notification
Change-Id: I05080afb8bd4249f8bea23512b25844fecbefeb9

commit_message:
Align required args for 'fuel2 graph upload'

Dissallow 'fuel2 graph uplod' command execution without
required args (-e ENV | -r RELEASE | -p PLUGIN), e.g.:
  usage: fuel2 graph upload [-h]
         (-e ENV | -r RELEASE | -p PLUGIN) [-t TYPE] -f FILE

Change-Id: I4fb1215874a849ea032afadb9604fca0dc0784a1
Closes-Bug: 1587837

commit_message:
Update metrics spec to reflect review comments

This addresses a few small spec changes required for metrics as
determined in code review.

Including:

commit_message:
Implement propose_rdo_promote CI periodic job

Background: during a cycle, we deploy OpenStack on centos7 from trunk
using RDO repositories, automatically built at each commit in OpenStack.

Currently, Puppet OpenStack CI manually promotes
puppet-openstack-integration every week, to latest URL. We would like to
automate this process with a daily periodic job so every day we would
have a promotion and we could detect which commit in OpenStack would
break our CI, and we could work on it quicker than usual, because
feedback would be daily.

This patch adds a periodic job, called
"propose-puppet-openstack-rdo-promote" that will execute
jenkins/scripts/propose_rdo_promote.sh script. The script has been
tested and already used manually.

Change-Id: I9b19a440325f609746a197676d3799aa0f60ce66

commit_message:
Use an image object, recorder object and status constants

Instead of using raw dicts and passing data around via
dictionaries (which makes it really hard to figure out
what is in those dictionaries at any point) prefer to
use objects. That way people can actually understand what
the object is supposed to be, vs guessing and/or having to
decipher its usage.

The same goes for raw string constants, prefer using
named constants instead.

Closes-Bug: #1586475

Change-Id: Ide179dc6593c50696d47a2d3d4cd000f343855d4

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary mock

In one of the unit tests, we unnecessarily mock os.path.join. This
seems to cause the test to hang on Python 3.4, as gettextutils will
hang when attempting to translate one of the messages logged by
the tested method.

For now, we'll just remove this mock as it's blocking the gate.
Still,We may have to understand better why we did not have this
issue before.

Change-Id: I00b0e1d2dd10a392096c35e81d402d5a4b0ef703

commit_message:
Cache service providers on token validation

On fernet token validation we rebuild the entire token catalog. This includes
rebuilding the service providers references in the token if using a federated
token. In the mitaka release, patches were added to cache user catalogs and
role assignments. This allows us to do the same thing for service providers,
which decreases the time spent in get_token_data() by 34%.

Co-Authored-By: Dolph Mathews <dolph.mathews@gmail.com>

Related-Bug: 1489061
Change-Id: I3dfe66880295ef36a18ca3e384191106b74be795

commit_message:
Set side bar content to be configurable

Sometimes (e.g. for the api-ref pages) the TOC should be in the side bar.
This allows this to be set as a theme option, but defaulting to
current behaviour - the new TOC will only be set
if a project sets the "sidebar_mode" option to "toc".

Change-Id: I9b93b671d4c32f5b237b0d79ae2be39059402d72

commit_message:
Hardening Nginx configuration

This commit contains some tweaks for the Nginx to prevent several
types of attacks, now we send to the client several HTTP headers
to enable client-side internal web browser protection mechanisms.
Also, we allow only required request methods for each service
provided by the server.

Change-Id: Idc60877c84f4b07617eaee0450fde4910e03f2e2
Closes-Bug: #1585203
Signed-off-by: Maksim Malchuk <mmalchuk@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Alex Schultz <aschultz@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit 264517e8784733acbd85253397cbddfb334614d6)

commit_message:
Lockdown pip when pip links are configured

The previous conditional was vague and overly tied
to the OSA inventory model. Deployers may want to lock down
pip to specific repositories that do not exist within
an OSA provided repository.

Alternatively, in a multi-region usage of OSA, the repository
may be a centralized service and therefore not present in
the dynamic inventory of a given region.

Change-Id: Ib5acd51435bd9432132c431d0b952bde41a6c890

commit_message:
Refactor revoke_model to remove circular dependency

In the process of caching service providers, a circular dependency was
uncovered between keystone's caching module and the revoke_model. This change
isolates the refactor to fix the circular dependency into it's own patch. A
separate follow on patch will add caching to service providers on token
creation and validation.

Change-Id: Iaa3c30d51270089b2d5999383d60ed0b2f7f56c8

commit_message:
Keep only actually required attributes in cluster context

We do not have clear boundary between node and cluster attributes,
and we cannot use whole master node state as cluster state because
it contains the node specific attributes too. The temporary
solution is add only list of nodes and product version to cluster
attributes, because only this attributes are needed as old state for
nodes, that do not have previous state.

Change-Id: I12ac64048c47a1afea03dc07b4c8ba3ba2c3ce2e
Closes-Bug: 1582247

commit_message:
Disable directory listing in the Nginx

Due to security reasons, sensitive information shouldn't be exposed.
Whenever possible we should disable directory listing in the Nginx:
 * in the local repos we show an empty page for dirs without
   an index file.
 * in the dashboard site directory listing disabled completely.

Change-Id: If4fb2ae1361697beb484b832c9e52507a34381ab
Closes-Bug: #1584797
Signed-off-by: Maksim Malchuk <mmalchuk@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit e3cee44a965e711823d95d5897193d1997359c8a)

commit_message:
Unified (one) error message for all invalid requests

It is possible based on the server error messages, to enumerate
directories and files on the application. This commit change the
default Nginx error messages to Unified one message with 200 (OK)
HTTP status code. For 404 (NOTFOUND) error we should preserve the
status code but provide the same Unified message because the
Package managers (in the Debian/Ubuntu at least) should know the
status of the file existence in the repos.

Change-Id: I6b996c5b1f8a1972379365571cf1f261e61b9ac5
Closes-Bug: #1585176
Signed-off-by: Maksim Malchuk <mmalchuk@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit c2066a9f9b2b273cf1861fa8af4d0e46e6ea6865)

commit_message:
Fix text font-family of admonitions.

This prepends a div with the correct font-awesome classes,
and leaves the title (Info / Warning etc) to inhert
fonts from the rest of the document.

This also removes the need for the prepended space to the title.
(as the content of the div is a space).

commit_message:
Lint YAML files

Currently most OpenStack code is linted, but YAML files are not. As a
result, sometimes YAML problems enter the code base (e.g., the key
duplicate fixed in change I7f2369adfb152fd2a74b9b105e969e653e592922).

This patch enables YAML linting in tox linting tests, using the
yamllint tool [1]. It checks syntax errors, key duplicates, and
cosmetic problems.

[1]: http://yamllint.readthedocs.org/

EDIT: It also fixes six errors (including key duplicates) that entered
the code base after the first fix change was merged.
(I7f2369adfb152fd2a74b9b105e969e653e592922)

Change-Id: Ie746230f28fe3ed0cf218201d5a3810f7bc44070

commit_message:
xen: Allow custom libvirt kernel in PV mode

Add a new configuration option under the "libvirt" section called
"xen_pv_kernel_path". If this option is set, the path is included
in the libvirt domain config under the <kernel> parameter.
Usually pygrub is used but pygrub doesn't support btrfs so
if a guest domain uses btrfs as filesystem, a different kernel needs
to be used. I.e. on a SUSE system the path to the kernel needed is
"/usr/lib/grub2/x86_64-xen/grub.xen".

Change-Id: I617c499457207c2795a664f087cbf525bbcccf04
Closes-Bug: #1531197

commit_message:
add experimental microversion selector

This adds experimental support for a microversion selector. The
interface for this may well change over time. To currently use this we
need 2 values in the sphinx conf.py to specify min and max
microversions. If you don't have those added, nothing is changed in
the UI.

Use at your own risk. However it's much easier to get feedback if we
have this in the package.

Change-Id: Iaf7e117ea5792bb3b60c1fd0ae416b241ab89d65

commit_message:
Fix live migration with shared storage

At the moment, when live migration is requested, we attempt to
copy the instance dvd disks and log files to the remote location,
other instance files being transparently copied by Hyper-V.

The issue is that we don't check whether shared storage is being
used, in which case this will fail.

This change adds this check.

Closes-Bug: #1565895

Change-Id: Ib646c90c830a1cd0e5401d14c6d400226b034f73
(cherry picked from commit ba2b0bbda58228e81c163c0b7cfef29cfaf13314)

commit_message:
Create planned VMs during LM only when needed

When performing a live migration, a planned VM is created every
time a volume is attached to the instance, while this is required
only in case of passthrough disks.

Skipping creating the planned VM when there are only disk files
attached takes out an unnecessary step, also dropping the Kerberos
constrained delegation requirement for environments where iSCSI/FC
based storage backends are not being used for Cinder.

Change-Id: Ib1aad4b5cf013b2ac62dc797ca6c53a2932f953f
(cherry picked from commit 56556f306d727b8402a5dd12bf35a7adcb9486ff)

commit_message:
Make import_file do its own cleanup

import_file is currently used only by the Rbd backend, and only for
importing a config file. The interface requires the caller to cleanup
after it, which means that code outside the Rbd driver is doing:

  if CONF.libvirt.images_type == 'rbd':
      os.unlink(configdrive_path)

This change turns import_file into a context manager, and implements
it for the only current users: NoBacking and Rbd. This allows us to
handle the required cleanup in the Rbd backend rather than pushing it
to the caller.

Implements: blueprint libvirt-instance-storage

Change-Id: Ibc39fb2d5e3b7e1d5d1fc0386db2fe633e8897af

commit_message:
Don't overwrite existing config file on resize/migrate

Resize and cold migrate were copying over an existing config disk,
converting it from raw to qcow2, then overwriting it with a new one.
Given that the original config disk is available and has already been
copied, we should just use that.

Closes-Bug: #1548884

Change-Id: I01dfd16a0f898b79e67dd98e989cb53a4bdd799f

commit_message:
Change checkers of config's applying order

Now for a node with multi-roles configs fot the same section
are merging by ID-priority. Thus last config for cinder will
be have higher priority and will rewrite compute config

Change-Id: Ic35a6c5efb05974dc7ab7ae36cc175a91471c778
Closes-Bug: #1587023

commit_message:
Add check_backing_from_func interface

Image.cache() currently implicitly does some backing file checks on an
existing disk. check_backing_from_func() performs the same function
for disks created by the output of a function (currently ephemeral and
swap disks), except it does it explicitly.

Note that the only backend which requires these checks is Qcow2, as no
other backend uses a backing file.

Implements: blueprint libvirt-instance-storage

Change-Id: I33b01038d1d1204a2871bd848594bafa1bfaf198

commit_message:
Adds Nova discoverable policy CLI spec

https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/discoverable-policy-cli

Not all users have the same set of privileges. Not all API endpoints
are enabled. Because of this, adding an nova-manage CLI subcommand that
lists the operations an user is allowed to use can be helpful. This spec
describes phase one of a two phased implementation. The first phase
will prove out the idea using a raw representation that will be
improved in the second phase.

Co-Authored-By: Chris Dent <cdent@anticdent.org>

Implements: blueprint discoverable-policy-cli

Change-Id: I973f1e0545c73d66ef17bed77c6dda5de007cb1e

commit_message:
Catch DriverLoadFailure for get_transport optional

new oslo.messaging 5.2.0 release will raise
oslo_messaging.transport.DriverLoadFailure if no existent transport
driver, hence breaks our code and unit test as well.

This patch fixes it by adding DriverLoadFailure to catch list.

Change-Id: I318d4b93beac9d1816fe4b5f9eb9de98e4debc04
Closes-Bug: #1588151

commit_message:
Hyper-V vTPM Devices

Windows / Hyper-V Server Technical Preview introduced the ability
to attach vTPM devices to the Hyper-V VMs, offering the users the
posibility to use it to enhance their security and system
integrity.

This commit implements adding vTPM devices to instances.

DocImpact

commit_message:
Take into account restriction's `strict` value

So far Nailgun always assumes that restrictions are strict, and doesn't
care about explicit (specified in restriction) `strict` value. This
commit fixes that, and if some restriction has an explicit `strict`
option it will be taken into account.

Change-Id: I5ef0e91f42cd708be5df56da461af4d7b568ae42
Closes-Bug: #1587773

subject: Add transport_url parameters for oslo.messaging
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-05-31 18:48:49.000000000', 'files': ['manifests/ceilometer.pp', 'releasenotes/notes/add_transport_url_parameters-29b87bdc9197a376.yaml', 'spec/classes/cinder_ceilometer_spec.rb', 'manifests/init.pp', 'spec/classes/cinder_spec.rb'], 'message': 'Add transport_url parameters for oslo.messaging

This commit adds the transport_url parameters for oslo.messaging. The
url is of the form:

  transport://user:pass@host1:port[,hostN:portN]/virtual_host

Where the transport scheme specifies the rpc or notification backend
as one of rabbit, amqp, zmq, etc. Oslo.messaging is deprecating the
host, port, and auth configuration options [1]. All drivers will get
these options via the transport_url.

This patch:
* use oslo::messaging::default resource
* use oslo::messaging::notifications resource
* add parameters for transport_url(s)
* update spec tests
* add feature release note

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/317285/

Change-Id: If5f30ba1944d897d2dd63539f4bb8a80e6c46c5e
'}]
commit_message:
Add transport_url parameters for oslo.messaging

This commit adds the transport_url parameters for oslo.messaging. The
url is of the form:

  transport://user:pass@host1:port[,hostN:portN]/virtual_host

Where the transport scheme specifies the rpc or notification backend
as one of rabbit, amqp, zmq, etc. Oslo.messaging is deprecating the
host, port, and auth configuration options [1]. All drivers will get
these options via the transport_url.

This patch:
* use oslo::messaging::default resource
* use oslo::messaging::notifications resource
* add parameters for transport_url(s)
* update spec tests
* add feature release note

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/317285/

Change-Id: If5f30ba1944d897d2dd63539f4bb8a80e6c46c5e

commit_message:
Config settings to support PCI-DSS

Configuration settings to support PCI-DSS:
1. Disable users based on given minimum number of days of inactivity.
2. Lockout a user if number of failed attempts exceeds given limit.
3. Lockout user for a given amount of time if locked out.
4. Expire a password after given amount of days has passed
5. Require the user to create passwords that do not match the past given
   number of iterations.
6. Limit the number of times a password can be changed per day.
7. Require password complexity

Co-Authored-By: Ron De Rose ronald.de.rose@intel.com

Partially-Implements: blueprint pci-dss

Change-Id: I3ed5ca466ad15eab3c6e75aff3bb59543ecaabaa

commit_message:
Reprioritize node statuses

* pending addition/pending deletion node states have bigger priority
  than node status and appropriate labels should be shown on a node panel
* pending addition/pending deletion states removed from node list
  sorting by node status

Closes-Bug: #1576590

subject: Update devstack configure in stable/mitaka branch
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-06-03 02:15:26.000000000', 'files': ['devstack/local.conf.node_1.sample', 'devstack/local.conf.sample', 'README.md', 'devstack/settings'], 'message': 'Update devstack configure in stable/mitaka branch

1.What is the problem:
The devstack configuration is still pointed to the master branch in
stable/mitaka branch

2.What needs to be fixed:
In the Tricircle stable/mitaka branch, the devstack configuration should
be changed to downlowd the code from the Tricircle stable/mitaka branch
but not from the master branch. And also use Mitaka Neutron release in
running devstack for version compatibility purpose but instead of the Neutron
master branch.

3.What is the purpose of this patch set:
The Tricircle stable/mitaka branch has no enough features to run the
Tricircle in production, but after this patch set is merged, we can make a
tag in this branch, and check whether the release publishing process works
or not. The release package publishing to PyPI job has been configured and
merged in the following patch set: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/323108/

Change-Id: Ic273eaa033dfb53fcd17e9e91945341bb9f88e58
Signed-off-by: Chaoyi Huang <joehuang@huawei.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Update devstack configure in stable/mitaka branch

1.What is the problem:
The devstack configuration is still pointed to the master branch in
stable/mitaka branch

2.What needs to be fixed:
In the Tricircle stable/mitaka branch, the devstack configuration should
be changed to downlowd the code from the Tricircle stable/mitaka branch
but not from the master branch. And also use Mitaka Neutron release in
running devstack for version compatibility purpose but instead of the Neutron
master branch.

3.What is the purpose of this patch set:
The Tricircle stable/mitaka branch has no enough features to run the
Tricircle in production, but after this patch set is merged, we can make a
tag in this branch, and check whether the release publishing process works
or not. The release package publishing to PyPI job has been configured and
merged in the following patch set: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/323108/

Change-Id: Ic273eaa033dfb53fcd17e9e91945341bb9f88e58
Signed-off-by: Chaoyi Huang <joehuang@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Update the version of LXC for centos7

This updates the version of LXC to the latest stable (2.0.1).
This is being done because issues exist when running LXC 1.x
within SystemD and how capabilities are handled. To resolve the
capability issues as seen here: [0] the version of LXC has been
updated. This change also pulls Centos 7 in line with the release
series of LXC found on Ubuntu 16.04.

This change will unblock the os_keystone PR [1].

[0] - http://logs.openstack.org/16/320216/10/experimental/gate-openstack-ansible-os_keystone-ansible-func-centos-7-nv/514118f/console.html#_2016-06-01_20_59_54_386
[1] - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/320216

Change-Id: I333fb1887339e8dc9ebf10ff137dda3cff629dc0
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-02 18:25:57.000000000', 'files': ['deployment/puppet/osnailyfacter/manifests/database/database_backend_wait.pp', 'tests/noop/spec/hosts/database/database_spec.rb', 'deployment/puppet/osnailyfacter/manifests/database/database.pp'], 'message': "Always wait for database backend

Previously when using the detached-database functionality, the various
tasks that require the database task on the primary controller will run
immediately after the primary controller database task has executed.
Because the wait for the mysql backend was included within the enabled
if block, when detached db is used the database task finishes
immediately without the database actually being ready. This change
takes the mysql backend wait code and puts it in it's own class that
can be included anywhere the mysql backend wait needs to occur.
Additionally this code can be leveraged as a task if necessary.

Change-Id: Ia1d45f45cbbd91b7c6cacd4aa46dae0a92e4156e
Closes-Bug: #1588387
"}]
commit_message:
Always wait for database backend

Previously when using the detached-database functionality, the various
tasks that require the database task on the primary controller will run
immediately after the primary controller database task has executed.
Because the wait for the mysql backend was included within the enabled
if block, when detached db is used the database task finishes
immediately without the database actually being ready. This change
takes the mysql backend wait code and puts it in it's own class that
can be included anywhere the mysql backend wait needs to occur.
Additionally this code can be leveraged as a task if necessary.

Change-Id: Ia1d45f45cbbd91b7c6cacd4aa46dae0a92e4156e
Closes-Bug: #1588387

commit_message:
Remove tripleo::loadbalancer

The split has been done on both undercloud & overcloud, they now use
tripleo::haproxy and tripleo::keepalived. We can move forward with
removing tripleo::loadbalancer and tripleo::loadbalancer::endpoint, not
used anymore.

Simplify tripleo::profile::base::loadbalancer to just include
tripleo::haproxy and rely on Hiera for parameters.

Change-Id: Ieeb1e94117ae9cb8b11320306de3a9b236bd989a

commit_message:
Remove use of template based config from cisco ml2 nexus plugin.

Change to modify the cisco ml2 nexus section to remove the use
of the erb template for configuring the per-nexus switch ML2
config sections.  The change adds 2 new defined types which
wrap neutron_plugin_ml2 resource usage.

Change-Id: I401371c9e5176de7ce19d4d4e878e9f2e69aab80
Closes-bug: #1495537
(cherry picked from commit 6dc74ac0e69d4bdd4da826189b6d6c2d2bc8e6a9)

commit_message:
Require swift package installation before swift user.

- The user 'swift' is being ensured without any restriction on openstack-swift
package, so it is highly potential that the user is created before package is
installed with /bin/bash instead of /sbin/nologin as shell.

Closes-bug: #1525243
Change-Id: I4c7b7afb7eefeda0379db631f14eb8c32cbe8671
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>
(cherry picked from commit b75290b54c2a802ce7a1bec57c1985fcb6da9f99)
(cherry picked from commit 8102ffa5fb344f45606af39509b232b5ee354704)

commit_message:
Add support for RabbitMQ connection heartbeat

Kilo oslo.messaging added heartbeating support for RabbitMQ
connections.  This patch adds support for this in Puppet modules
by managing the oslo_messaging_rabbit/heartbeat_timeout_threshold
and oslo_messaging_rabbit/heartbeat_rate settings.

Also, update all rabbit-related parameters to move to the
oslo_messaging_rabbit section in keystone.conf, from the DEFAULT
section.

Change-Id: I4d78a3c67396744fe1f643b857d889cb0ee0ca49
Closes-bug: 1467667

commit_message:
Add support for RabbitMQ connection heartbeat

Kilo oslo.messaging added heartbeating support for RabbitMQ
connections.  This patch adds support for this in Puppet modules
by managing the oslo_messaging_rabbit/heartbeat_timeout_threshold
and oslo_messaging_rabbit/heartbeat_rate settings.

Change-Id: I19c82aacf83e5a4f7c9c5fbf76527f9713d6e846
Closes-bug: 1467667
(cherry picked from commit dde3c5134f9a972d2b82d11d8966c52bb84a38e1)

commit_message:
Add support for swift-object-expirer service

The swift-object-expirer service was not supported by
puppet-swift. Adding support by creating a new class
(swift::objectexpirer), and its associated custom type/provider.

Change-Id: I498ffe525a7316c0091e4c9d8b7d9658234231f6

commit_message:
[networking] Minor formating improvement

* "``.``." is not easy to read because it will be rendered into
  ".." (double period). This commit improves readability a bit.
* "Suggestion:" in intro-os-networking-features.rst is meaningless.
  The paragraph describes what we need to do in advance.
* Add commas to highligh a clause of an example.
* config-ml2-plug-in.rst: add a blank line to insert a line break.
* scenario-classic-mt.rst: add missing 'on'.
* scenario-classic-mt.rst: Change "IDs" to "ID ranges".
  "ID ranges" is easier to understand and it is already used
  in other places.

Change-Id: Ie098be8c7924e80f9830065af809dc91ecf39fe1

commit_message:
Check real network_metadata hash instead of nodes length

Use real hash data, cause in case of just calculating nodes count,
expression will give false negative result in case of simultaneously
removing one and add another controller.

Change-Id: I5d11d7cca5bf4730730eb27f3fd15e945d6cc81e
Closes-Bug: #1587485
(cherry picked from commit 530353f610c16fe76fd196910b1df3144bebb79a)

subject: zuul/layout: update tripleo jobs for Puppet CI
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-05-10 21:53:50.000000000', 'files': ['zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': "zuul/layout: update tripleo jobs for Puppet CI

* Add upgrade job for puppet-pacemaker beside HA job. Having both
  scenarios make sense for such a module, we need to keep testing both
  jobs. It won't cost a lot of resources, since patches in
  puppet-pacemaker are not every day.
* Add upgrade job for puppet-mistral, since it's now enabled by default
  on the undercloud.
* Add upgrade job for puppet-sahara, since it's now enabled by default
  on the overcloud.
* For all other modules that had TripleO jobs, replace nonha job by
  upgrade job. We figured that the upgrade job provides a more valuable
  feedback than non ha:
    - it runs Pacemaker so a more complex architecture is tested, more
      real to production.
    - it performs upgrade testing from previous state of TripleO, so we
      will detect breakages earlier, and give a more interesting
      feedback loop.

This patch needs validation from TripleO PTL & TripleO CI gurus (at
least Derekh).

Change-Id: I75821612eb6a2a7461f0be52a976e881995479a2
"}]
commit_message:
zuul/layout: update tripleo jobs for Puppet CI

* Add upgrade job for puppet-pacemaker beside HA job. Having both
  scenarios make sense for such a module, we need to keep testing both
  jobs. It won't cost a lot of resources, since patches in
  puppet-pacemaker are not every day.
* Add upgrade job for puppet-mistral, since it's now enabled by default
  on the undercloud.
* Add upgrade job for puppet-sahara, since it's now enabled by default
  on the overcloud.
* For all other modules that had TripleO jobs, replace nonha job by
  upgrade job. We figured that the upgrade job provides a more valuable
  feedback than non ha:
    - it runs Pacemaker so a more complex architecture is tested, more
      real to production.
    - it performs upgrade testing from previous state of TripleO, so we
      will detect breakages earlier, and give a more interesting
      feedback loop.

This patch needs validation from TripleO PTL & TripleO CI gurus (at
least Derekh).

commit_message:
Ensure db-sync Execs are run when Galera is ready

This patch is a first implementation of smart orchestration to deploy
Galera & run db-sync in a same step of TripleO deployment.

The goal is to tell Puppet to wait for Galera being ready before running
OpenStack db-sync execs.

The patch in dependency is an example of implementation in
puppet-sahara, where I noticed some HA jobs were failing because Galera
was not ready and Sahara tried to run db-sync.

If we merge this patch, we'll hopefully be able to reduce the number of
steps and accelerate the deployments and upgrades, because we'll use
Puppet orchestration functions.

Change-Id: Id4f7634b14c9360460c4e57f024eaef79576d062
Depends-On: I8795a883821949428d3f61e2f74b04ce5592f014

subject: Don't hold the connection when reply fail
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-02 12:00:07.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_messaging/_drivers/amqpdriver.py', 'oslo_messaging/_drivers/impl_rabbit.py'], 'message': "Don't hold the connection when reply fail

This change moves the reply retry code to upper layer
to be able to release the connection while we wait between
two retries.

In the worse scenario, a client waits for more than 30 replies
and died/restart, the server tries to send this 30 replies to this
this client and can wait too 60s per replies. During this
replies for other clients are just stuck.

This change fixes that.

Related-bug: #1477914
Closes-bug: #1521958

Change-Id: I0d3c16ea6d2c1da143de4924b3be41d1cea159bd
"}]
commit_message:
Don't hold the connection when reply fail

This change moves the reply retry code to upper layer
to be able to release the connection while we wait between
two retries.

In the worse scenario, a client waits for more than 30 replies
and died/restart, the server tries to send this 30 replies to this
this client and can wait too 60s per replies. During this
replies for other clients are just stuck.

This change fixes that.

Related-bug: #1477914
Closes-bug: #1521958

Change-Id: I0d3c16ea6d2c1da143de4924b3be41d1cea159bd

commit_message:
Set proper cache backend for keystone.conf

* "memcache_pool" was a workaround for
  eventlet. As we don't use eventlet we
  should use proper backend for caching
* cache backend can be configured via hiera
* package installation provided by upstream
  puppet-oslo module
* noop tests are updated

Closes-bug: #1581133

Change-Id: If86ce795a8f53d8e93b6e5eeab79f9231621ee0e
Depends-On: I2e6a705971761754c59b4069b5dfdfd1dfd7f00f

commit_message:
Fix mistral installation in devstack

After pip upgrading following error has occured during
mistral installation:
Invalid requirement, parse error at "'[-e]'"

I assume that this is because of extra '-e' flag that was passed
in mistral script and that is redundant ('-e' flag will be added
automatically in setup_develop function).

Change-Id: Ifed16935b045c723881a9da157a8759eea421c2c

commit_message:
Add quickstart roles requirements file

The shift away from CAT to TripleO-quickstart requires an additional
requirements file. This file allows for consumption of many roles
used for a variety of post-deployment changes e.g. collect-logs,
scale, validate, etc.

commit_message:
libvirt: Skip CPU compatibility check for emulated guests

Comparing host to guest CPU model for emulated guests (<domain
type='qemu'>) should not matter -- in this mode the CPU is fully
emulated in software and no hardware acceleration, like KVM, is
involved.

So, skip the CPU compatibility check for the QEMU domain type,
and retain it for KVM guests.

Conflicts:
    nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py

    (Remove references to instance object in
    'test_compare_cpu_virt_type_qemu'.)

Closes-Bug: #1588003

Co-Authored-By: Daniel P. Berrange <berrange@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I8b782678a6dfa7bcfc203381037e1df4475c3194
(cherry picked from commit afa31e67c3b7f8999da179b78a7051d70ca126bf)

commit_message:
libvirt: add method "migrate" to Guest's object

In order to provides a higher level of abstraction between libvirt
driver and libvirt api call. This method handle guest migration by
choosing which method should be called based from params passed to
that method.

Implements: blueprint libvirt-clean-driver
Change-Id: I942864853dfba2be62bc137f40c25396961d7cb9

commit_message:
Handle ovs_socket_mem as list

Due to yaml dump/load incomsistency, string like '1,2,3,4' will be
dumped without quotes and loaded without commas. To fix it, socket
memory per NUMA will be passed as a list.

Change-Id: I579c43a0e8a391092f33a755e18b06ef8ed1a62e
Closes-Bug: #1587898

commit_message:
Add fallback prevention to mysql in haproxy config

Using sticky-table + stick on dst prevents fallback to active node in
scenario where it comes back from being down. This may lead to sql
connections from openstack services to different mysql nodes.

This patch also removes hash-type and balance option as stickiness
is being done with sticky-table.

Change-Id: Ibc2fb4fa5a1938aec447694638c4c9e99edbba53
Closes-bug: #1529937
(cherry picked from commit fa8f1f7746bf639f73d09964e482bd7847180d1d)

commit_message:
Use default value of kombu_reconnect_delay for all services

Current reconnection time is 5.0 which is pretty long.
This patch switches kombu_reconnect_delay to its default
value - 1.0 which is the same for all services.

Change-Id: I168a440a755b197ca69ee3fa932b163e3915d5cd
Closes-bug: #1560097

commit_message:
Check real network_metadata hash instead of nodes length

Use real hash data, cause in case of just calculating nodes count,
expression will give false negative result in case of simultaneously
removing one and add another controller.

Change-Id: I5d11d7cca5bf4730730eb27f3fd15e945d6cc81e
Closes-Bug: #1587485

commit_message:
Add NetworkMultiDelete class to support bulk deletion in networkv2

Add basic class "NetworkMultiDelete" in network/commom.py.
We can use it in every delete commands of networkv2 to
support bulk deletion and error handling following the
rules in doc/source/command-errors.rst.

Partially-Implements: blueprint multi-argument-network

commit_message:
Disabe WEAK DHE ciphers to leave TLSv1 support

We should disable WEAK DHE ciphers completely but leave TLSv1 support
for old OSes and outdated browsers, they would use ECDHE ciphers.

Change-Id: Ifab14ce22d17cbc84275dd9225252817e3131ac4
Closes-Bug: #1497195
Signed-off-by: Maksim Malchuk <mmalchuk@mirantis.com>
(cherry picked from commit 2d3856ddfc0f9599bed1540225db516bcb367587)

subject: Bump up oslo messaging version
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-06-01 07:23:57.000000000', 'files': ['global-requirements.txt'], 'message': "Bump up oslo messaging version

Change I5f23e23644e90919cb67f81fc306ee85c5e09974 has fixed issue with
message acknowledgement where the messages are acknowledged only when
it is being processed and not when it is being queued. If the serving
process crashes, the messages can be recieved by other peer processes or
when the dead process restarts.

This is needed in Heat where we don't want the converge messages to be
lost when a heat-engine fails/crashes.

Change-Id: I059b766dea16aa299b58ada07ed3a398a9a164a1
"}]
commit_message:
Bump up oslo messaging version

Change I5f23e23644e90919cb67f81fc306ee85c5e09974 has fixed issue with
message acknowledgement where the messages are acknowledged only when
it is being processed and not when it is being queued. If the serving
process crashes, the messages can be recieved by other peer processes or
when the dead process restarts.

This is needed in Heat where we don't want the converge messages to be
lost when a heat-engine fails/crashes.

Change-Id: I059b766dea16aa299b58ada07ed3a398a9a164a1

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-03 06:27:40.000000000', 'files': ['neutron_lbaas/services/loadbalancer/plugin.py'], 'message': 'Author: liujingzte <liu.jing5@zte.com.cn>
Date:   Thu Jun 3 13:46:00 2016

In function create_listener,_check_pool_loadbalancer_match is used to
make sure default_pool has the same lb_id as given.
When a listener is created with default_pool_id and no lb_id,
lb_id is set to default_pool.loadbalancer.id
So the check _check_pool_loadbalancer_match does repeated.

I want to skip this extra check in the condition that a listener is
created with default_pool_id and no lb_id.

Change-Id: Id01de2c6c886acbdeef40d4e9d05aa11ec7947bf
Closes-Bug: #1588118
'}]
commit_message:
Author: liujingzte <liu.jing5@zte.com.cn>
Date:   Thu Jun 3 13:46:00 2016

In function create_listener,_check_pool_loadbalancer_match is used to
make sure default_pool has the same lb_id as given.
When a listener is created with default_pool_id and no lb_id,
lb_id is set to default_pool.loadbalancer.id
So the check _check_pool_loadbalancer_match does repeated.

I want to skip this extra check in the condition that a listener is
created with default_pool_id and no lb_id.

Change-Id: Id01de2c6c886acbdeef40d4e9d05aa11ec7947bf
Closes-Bug: #1588118

Commit 10d54216871fde27172fbcb1a3c9bfec59b824c2 added the
ability to query volume_attachments by host and instance_uuid.

Minor bug however is that the original implementation also used
a "first()" filter, so regardless of how many attachments might
exist, only one was being returned.

The volume_attachments object code assumes we receive a list, as
do a number of other places.  So, this patch changes the names of
those get methods to "get_all_by_xxx" to eliminate any confusion
and updates things to use the list appropriately.

Change-Id: I63e4faf8a7ee3528a4dfbd7bf4e61b607ad86841
Closes-Bug: #1585690
'}]
commit_message:
Fix attachment_get_by_* to return entire list

Commit 10d54216871fde27172fbcb1a3c9bfec59b824c2 added the
ability to query volume_attachments by host and instance_uuid.

Minor bug however is that the original implementation also used
a "first()" filter, so regardless of how many attachments might
exist, only one was being returned.

The volume_attachments object code assumes we receive a list, as
do a number of other places.  So, this patch changes the names of
those get methods to "get_all_by_xxx" to eliminate any confusion
and updates things to use the list appropriately.

Change-Id: I63e4faf8a7ee3528a4dfbd7bf4e61b607ad86841
Closes-Bug: #1585690

'}]
commit_message:
Ensure nova-network service is up before creating networks

https://review.openstack.org/229895 made sure nova networks could
only be created if the nova-network service was enabled. However,
it is still possible that Puppet tries to create them before the
service is started.

This patch should be backported to stable/mitaka and stable/liberty.

Change-Id: Iaf21b70f274d2c5769c6bb117697efe9e74873fd

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2016-06-01 09:13:21.000000000', 'files': ['files/fuel-ha-utils/ocf/neutron-ovs-agent'], 'message': "Moved 3 second delay in ovs-agent start script.

Currently, pacemaker checks status of ovs-agent by verifying its
PID after the start of an ovs-agent process, this may lead to
invalid status if the process fails to start.

This commit moves 3 second delay from the end of the 'while' cycle
of the status check to the beging, to let neutron-ovs-agent resource
set correct status

commit_message:
Moved 3 second delay in ovs-agent start script.

Currently, pacemaker checks status of ovs-agent by verifying its
PID after the start of an ovs-agent process, this may lead to
invalid status if the process fails to start.

This commit moves 3 second delay from the end of the 'while' cycle
of the status check to the beging, to let neutron-ovs-agent resource
set correct status

Change-Id: I1678ef82a76c6e820df3f736bc538439966e5f94
Closes-Bug: #1585824

commit_message:
Add fallback prevention to mysql in haproxy config

Using sticky-table + stick on dst prevents fallback to active node in
scenario where it comes back from being down. This may lead to sql
connections from openstack services to different mysql nodes.

This patch also removes hash-type and balance option as stickiness
is being done with sticky-table.

Change-Id: Ibc2fb4fa5a1938aec447694638c4c9e99edbba53
Closes-bug: #1529937

Set same values from ironic-compute and openstack-controller

variables from different manifests.

and openstack-controller task.

commit_message:
Add API version to identity endpoint URLs

This change adds the Keystone API version to the identity endpoint URL
retrieved from Keystone's endpoint list. This is neccessary in Kilo and
later, since identity endpoint URLs retrieved from Keystone no longer
contain the API version path they used to contain until Juno. See
https://bugs.launchpad.net/horizon/+bug/1508421 for a detailed analysis
of the problem.

Change-Id: Ieff5a6cdd1ad352a9731d46785802e8c36adcdd1
Closes-Bug: 1508421
(cherry picked from commit 58ce9d7edeac81dbd7e7f77efde33c97e8d1e00c)

subject: Fix "Add API version to identity endpoint URLs"
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-03-08 14:17:35.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_auth/tests/tests.py', 'openstack_auth/utils.py'], 'message': 'Fix "Add API version to identity endpoint URLs"

Change Ieff5a6cdd1ad352a9731d46785802e8c36adcdd1 introduced an
uncomplete fix when trying to fix the auth_url.
Given the case that a auth url already has a version included, an extra
version was added. This leads to messages in the keystone.log that
horizon is trying to authenticate with "POST /v3/v3/auth/tokens
HTTP/1.1".
Use urlparse correctly and also add a testcase for fix_auth_url_version().

Change-Id: I80fb310d95e8fdab1212fc5b092a37fd7b26a37a
Closes-Bug: 1508421
(cherry picked from commit e008112d0f964b00bd5cb633262365ebc7f9395b)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix "Add API version to identity endpoint URLs"

Change Ieff5a6cdd1ad352a9731d46785802e8c36adcdd1 introduced an
uncomplete fix when trying to fix the auth_url.
Given the case that a auth url already has a version included, an extra
version was added. This leads to messages in the keystone.log that
horizon is trying to authenticate with "POST /v3/v3/auth/tokens
HTTP/1.1".
Use urlparse correctly and also add a testcase for fix_auth_url_version().

Change-Id: I80fb310d95e8fdab1212fc5b092a37fd7b26a37a
Closes-Bug: 1508421
(cherry picked from commit e008112d0f964b00bd5cb633262365ebc7f9395b)

commit_message:
Unscoped PKI token should no longer be hashed multiple times.

When token hashing is used with pki tokens, the unscoped token
gets re-hashed when switching project. This fix checks
if the unscoped token needs to be hashed before doing so.

The project list operation when switching project in horizon
failed because the unscoped token could for example be an
md5 of an md5.
(modified for stable/kilo branch)

Change-Id: I6d0086cebb0326dd3052b6e1b251549953a20944
Closes-Bug: #1487372

commit_message:
Disabe WEAK DHE ciphers to leave TLSv1 support

We should disable WEAK DHE ciphers completely but leave TLSv1 support
for old OSes and outdated browsers, they would use ECDHE ciphers.

Change-Id: Ifab14ce22d17cbc84275dd9225252817e3131ac4
Closes-Bug: #1497195

commit_message:
Added ability to update PXE DHCP parameters after deploy

It's possible to change PXE settings on post deploy stage, but, in fact,
dnsmasq configuration will not be changed. This patch introduce puppet
call to get these changes applied.

Function puppetApply was refactored to return Bool value,
previously it has returned None or False.

Change-Id: I3fc7097035f492ad24483205cedc0d2c773af24b
Closes-Bug: #1500667
Depends-On: I9200c90747dba1e5c5b4e5457e423cb4c3ff3062

commit_message:
UCA support for nova compute

This changes adds the Ubuntu Cloud Archive repo support for the nova
compute kvm. UCA repo is important to support architecture ppc64le
since the default Ubuntu trusty repo does not contain the all required
packages for libvirt-bin.

Change-Id: Ic1e7619b48a9b12ba876f83507497cf1e557223a

subject: Run {name}-announce-release for Puppet OpenStack modules
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-06-01 20:37:44.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/jobs/projects.yaml', 'zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': 'Run {name}-announce-release for Puppet OpenStack modules

The goal of this patch is use openstack-server-release-jobs for all
Puppet OpenStack modules and have some consistency with other project
releases.

It does:
* Add {name}-announce-release jobs to all Puppet modules.
  Note: puppet-pacemaker was missing the bits for release management, we
  add them in this patch.
* Rename puppet-tarball-jobs to puppet-branch-tarball-jobs and keep only
  {name}-branch-tarball in post pipeline. Other jobs are managed by
  openstack-server-release-jobs layout.
* Use puppet-branch-tarball-jobs and openstack-server-release-jobs
  layouts for all our Puppet OpenStack modules.

Change-Id: Idba8e7b8966ebf814346e8360e857af6d6c3de95
'}]
commit_message:
Run {name}-announce-release for Puppet OpenStack modules

The goal of this patch is use openstack-server-release-jobs for all
Puppet OpenStack modules and have some consistency with other project
releases.

It does:
* Add {name}-announce-release jobs to all Puppet modules.
  Note: puppet-pacemaker was missing the bits for release management, we
  add them in this patch.
* Rename puppet-tarball-jobs to puppet-branch-tarball-jobs and keep only
  {name}-branch-tarball in post pipeline. Other jobs are managed by
  openstack-server-release-jobs layout.
* Use puppet-branch-tarball-jobs and openstack-server-release-jobs
  layouts for all our Puppet OpenStack modules.

Change-Id: Idba8e7b8966ebf814346e8360e857af6d6c3de95

commit_message:
Create separate ACL groups for murano-apps project

After several meetings with Murano, Infra and App Catalog teams there was
decided to create new groups murano-apps-* for review/release/ci for
murano-apps repository. It is necessary for future growing this project
and involving new contributors of new Murano applications.

As a start review from previous approach please add murano-core group to
all new groups.

Change-Id: I881a6c3aff2de96b288c74a6bc4474ca70aa26e1

subject: Add Kolla liberty to the release repo
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-26 22:35:23.000000000', 'files': ['deliverables/liberty/kolla.yaml'], 'message': "Add Kolla liberty to the release repo

Kolla joined the big tent during the Liberty cycle.  As a result,
we weren't following semver versioning, but copying other projects
versioning scheme which at the time was liberty-1, liberty-2,
liberty-3 liberty-rc1, liberty-rc2, and 1.0.0-liberty.

Should we retag all of these tags with semver versioning matching
what we did in our Mitaka series?  Liberty was our first 1.0.0
release.  THe prior releases in icehosue/juno/kilo were pure R&D
but now our architecture has stabilized to the point in Liberty
that we consider it a 1.0.0 release.  If we do retag with semver,
should I ask openstack-infra to delete the existing tags?

Thanks
-steve

Change-Id: I5885cbda16594d1b39aade5412be0e9e3fc959fa
"}]
commit_message:
Add Kolla liberty to the release repo

Kolla joined the big tent during the Liberty cycle.  As a result,
we weren't following semver versioning, but copying other projects
versioning scheme which at the time was liberty-1, liberty-2,
liberty-3 liberty-rc1, liberty-rc2, and 1.0.0-liberty.

Should we retag all of these tags with semver versioning matching
what we did in our Mitaka series?  Liberty was our first 1.0.0
release.  THe prior releases in icehosue/juno/kilo were pure R&D
but now our architecture has stabilized to the point in Liberty
that we consider it a 1.0.0 release.  If we do retag with semver,
should I ask openstack-infra to delete the existing tags?

Thanks
-steve

Change-Id: I5885cbda16594d1b39aade5412be0e9e3fc959fa

commit_message:
Remove skip test logic for project-config

After talking to clarkb, it has become too much work (and churn) to
justify our skip logic on project-config. As a result, we'll now run
all our jobs regardless of the patch to project-config.

Change-Id: I130f86d327302b5b251e81651a3a19acf84c5f51
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Remove API races from migrate and retype

We have a window of opportunity for races in API's migrate_volume and
retype methods.

This patch removes these windows of opportunity using compare-and-swap
for DB updates in the API.

Specs: https://review.openstack.org/232599/

Implements: blueprint cinder-volume-active-active-support
Closes-Bug: #1493476
Closes-Bug: #1494466
Change-Id: I2de07b9cf7f0d670e4c531e8be9ae1c879c890f6

subject: Use a task model and dumb workers
revisions:
[{'number': 11, 'created': '2016-06-02 18:21:16.000000000', 'files': ['kolla/common/task.py', 'kolla/cmd/build.py', 'kolla/tests/test_build.py'], 'message': 'Use a task model and dumb workers

Instead of having smart workers that need to know
about the full logic of how they operate and what
they will do which makes it hard to reuse parts of
those workers switch the model so that workers are
dumb and they just run tasks which themselves can
request additional tasks to run when succesful.

This makes it more consistent when tasks are to
be retried and also makes it easier to know which
task is running and when.

Less specialized workers == good.

Closes-Bug: #1586474

Change-Id: Ie7b7303b8bf2a80b3e26b6d4ffc27787f8c794d6
'}]
commit_message:
Use a task model and dumb workers

Instead of having smart workers that need to know
about the full logic of how they operate and what
they will do which makes it hard to reuse parts of
those workers switch the model so that workers are
dumb and they just run tasks which themselves can
request additional tasks to run when succesful.

This makes it more consistent when tasks are to
be retried and also makes it easier to know which
task is running and when.

Less specialized workers == good.

Closes-Bug: #1586474

Change-Id: Ie7b7303b8bf2a80b3e26b6d4ffc27787f8c794d6

commit_message:
Connectivity check from host via multiply methods

Adds ability to select differnt connectivity checks with different
protocol methods.
Adds wrapprs to choose connectivty checks to run for each
connectivity protocol.
Fix subprocess use to prevent deadlock.

Add test to test_network_basic_ops (test_network_protocols) for checking
different protocol connectivity permissions.

This patch is required for https://review.openstack.org/#/c/102633/
With this patch we can resume working on it.

Related-Bug: #1298472

Change-Id: Ifb053031ea17cdfd45e0ecfca1ae2f237c725126

commit_message:
Oject Storage API tests: make X-Timestamp checks optional.

Implement the configuration option "object_storage.strict_mode"
to verify only the behaviours and traits described in the document
"OpenStack Object Storage API v1" which is availble at:
http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-objectstorage-v1.html

The OpenStack Object Storage API v1 does not mention that
X-Timestamp HTTP header is mandatory, so disable the checks
for it in the strict mode.

Closes-Bug: #1422728
Change-Id: If0fd0cee78cfec63fce60f9032054bf460b80c97

commit_message:
Define default build timeout for required services

Some services like baremetal, database etc do not define their build
timeout in config file. There should be some configurable default
build_timeout for such services.

This patch defines the default build timeout and interval in config file
and use the same as default one for service clients.

Change-Id: I05818f7b6b71edf66023ebe982e1594a8c239cd8

commit_message:
Cleanup test_networks.py inheritance and class split

Previously the test classes defined in tempest.api.network.test_networks
was a real mess, there was class inheritance where it didn't belong,
which resulted in duplicate tests. Additionally, the structural split
of files was completely ignored, which resulted in way to many test
classes being dumped in there. This commit cleans this up be fixing the
inheritance between test classes and moving test classes to separate
files where it makes sense.

Change-Id: I29d67136f6191310ac5e18301864c40454fc200f

commit_message:
Enhanced connectivity check using multiple protocols

Adds ability to select different connectivity checks on different
protocol methods. This is done by introuducing a new config option
security_group.protocols, specifying which protocols are to be
tested. Default value is ['icmp'], so that the functionality
stays the same, unless other values are set in the config
option in tempest.conf.
Adds wrappers to choose connectivity checks to run for each
connectivity protocol.
Adds the ability to implement multi-protocol isolation checks.

This commit is useful for hypervisors which do not support
ICMP security group rules or cannot create stateful ICMP security
group rules (e.g.: Hyper-V cannot create stateful ICMP rules,
but can create stateful rules for UDP and TCP), thus, being able
to pass the tests with their supported protocols.

This patch is required for https://review.openstack.org/#/c/102633/
With this patch we can resume working on it.

Co-Authored-By: Claudiu Belu <cbelu@cloudbasesolutions.com>

Related-Bug: #1298472

Change-Id: I85be686bae4c38b21f4e79cffbb19c5b862066b2

commit_message:
Skip test_shelve_instance in multinode case

Shelve/Unshelve across different nodes isn't working reliably. SKip the test for
now so that we can keep working on stabilizing the multihost job so that
we can make it gating as soon as possible.

getting the job gating and default instead of fixing shelve/unshelve

commit_message:
Add unit test to ensure sane test class subclassing

After adding idempotent ids to all test methods to track tests across
renames and file moves we want to ensure that subclasses are actually
using inheritance in valid cases. Which for right now is different API
versions, IP versions, or in the case of heat YAML vs AWS templates.
This commit adds a test to do a quick sanity check to ensure that the
class names at least diffs between test_ids for subclasses are only
different in valid ways.

subject: Switch use of map() to a list comprehension
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-07-16 17:48:45.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/tests/test_tenant_isolation.py'], 'message': 'Switch use of map() to a list comprehension

Because of a behavior change in the way map works on python3 we had
to explicitly cast each use of map() to a list to emulate the behavior
we expected in python2. However a list comprehension could be used
without doing list(map()) which is a slightly friendlier syntax. This
commit switches all the uses of map() with a wrapping list() to just
be a comprehension.

Change-Id: Id0a989c2b97d81473a380474c973ad380f2c825e
'}]
commit_message:
Switch use of map() to a list comprehension

Because of a behavior change in the way map works on python3 we had
to explicitly cast each use of map() to a list to emulate the behavior
we expected in python2. However a list comprehension could be used
without doing list(map()) which is a slightly friendlier syntax. This
commit switches all the uses of map() with a wrapping list() to just
be a comprehension.

Change-Id: Id0a989c2b97d81473a380474c973ad380f2c825e

Cleanup will only support test accounts moving forward, tenant isolation
and standard tempest and alternate tempest users and tenants are also
no longer supported by cleanup (typically these are named demo and
alt_demo). If CONF.auth.test_accounts_file is populated, cleanup will
handle these accounts in the same way the standard tempest and alternate
tempest users and tenants were handled in the past. If the test accounts
have not been configured or the test accounts file cannot be loaded,
cleanup will exit with an error.

When cleanup is run in standard mode objects left over by a tempest run
are deleted from the test account tenants but the test account tenants
and users themselves are NOT deleted so that tempest can be re-run easily.

If the --delete-tempest-test-accounts flag is set when running cleanup
the test accounts, tenants, networks, and routers will be deleted.

Lastly cleanup will no longer support tenant isolation.  If
allow_tenant_isolation is set to True in tempest.conf cleanup
will terminate.

Change-Id: I7f8f878bebec9fbdc6ab64a092780a0add3b1e4a
'}]
commit_message:
Make cleanup test accounts aware

Cleanup will only support test accounts moving forward, tenant isolation
and standard tempest and alternate tempest users and tenants are also
no longer supported by cleanup (typically these are named demo and
alt_demo). If CONF.auth.test_accounts_file is populated, cleanup will
handle these accounts in the same way the standard tempest and alternate
tempest users and tenants were handled in the past. If the test accounts
have not been configured or the test accounts file cannot be loaded,
cleanup will exit with an error.

When cleanup is run in standard mode objects left over by a tempest run
are deleted from the test account tenants but the test account tenants
and users themselves are NOT deleted so that tempest can be re-run easily.

If the --delete-tempest-test-accounts flag is set when running cleanup
the test accounts, tenants, networks, and routers will be deleted.

Lastly cleanup will no longer support tenant isolation.  If
allow_tenant_isolation is set to True in tempest.conf cleanup
will terminate.

Change-Id: I7f8f878bebec9fbdc6ab64a092780a0add3b1e4a

This test suite verifies that the instance metrics are properly published
and collected and have non-zero values. The verification is done via the
ceilometer API.

Waiting for the ceilometer compute agent to poll the resources is crucial,
otherwise the test suite will fail due to the fact that no samples would
be found published before checking the samples.

The ceilometer agent's polling interval should have the same value as
the test suite's polled_metric_delay. This can be done in two ways:
a. Configure tempest's polled_metric_delay, by adding the following
line in tempest.conf, in the telemetry-feature-enabled section:
    polled_metric_delay = <desired value>
b. Set the interval value in pipeline.yaml on the compute node to the
desired value and restart the ceilometer compute agent.

The second method is preferred, as the interval value defined in
pipeline.yaml is 600 seconds, which would mean each test would last
at least 10 minutes.

Change-Id: Icf41f119fb1393ea3508f12f2f065ecaea445b07
